 Here's the full walkthrough of every screen based on your actual code:

  ---
  First Time Setup — Create a Budget

  When you open the Dashboard for a new year (e.g. 2026) and no budget exists yet, you'll see:

  ▎ "No budget for 2026 yet" with a Create Budget 2026 button.

  Click it → a dialog pops up asking for:
  - Beginning Spending Balance — how much cash/bank money you're starting the year with (e.g. ₹50,000)
  - Beginning Savings Balance — how much is already in your savings/FD (e.g. ₹2,00,000)

  These are your opening balances. After hitting Create, the dashboard loads.

  ---
  Tab 1 — Dashboard (Annual Overview)

  What you see:
  - 4 summary cards at the top: Total Income, Total Expenses, NET Balance, Spending Balance
  - A grid of 12 month cards (Jan–Dec), each showing income (green), expenses (red), and net for that month
  - Arrows at the top to navigate between years (< 2025 / 2026 >)

  What to do:
  - Tap any month card (e.g. Apr) → opens the Monthly View for that month, showing a day-by-day breakdown with running balance
  - Pull down to refresh

  ---
  The + Button (Add Transaction)

  The blue + button on the Dashboard opens the Add Transaction screen. This is how you record every rupee spent or earned.

  Fields to fill:
  1. Date — tap to pick a date (restricted to the current month)
  2. Category Group — e.g. "Food & Dining", "Income", "Savings"
  3. Category — sub-category under the group (e.g. "Groceries" under Food & Dining)
  4. Amount — in ₹
  5. Payment Method — Cash / SBI / ICICI / RBL / HDFC / HDFC Rupay / Yes Rupay
  6. Spent By — which family member (only shown if multiple users exist)
  7. Note — optional description

  Hit Save Transaction — it's saved and the dashboard updates.

  ---
  Tab 2 — Planning (Budget Targets)

  What it is: Where you set how much you plan to spend in each category for a month — your budget targets.

  What you see:
  - Month dropdown + year arrows at the top to switch months
  - All expense and savings category groups listed as expandable cards (income is hidden — you don't "plan" income here)
  - Each category has a ₹ input field on the right

  What to do:
  1. Select the month (e.g. April 2026)
  2. Expand a group (e.g. "Food & Dining") → type planned amounts for each category (e.g. Groceries ₹8000, Restaurants ₹3000)
  3. Hit Save All at the bottom — saves all targets at once
  4. Copy Previous button — copies last month's targets into this month (saves re-typing if budget is similar month to month)

  These planned amounts show as the "Planned" column on the Dashboard vs the "Actual" you actually spent.

  ---
  Tab 3 — Reports

  Three sub-tabs inside Reports:

  By Category (pie chart)
  - Shows expense spending broken down by category group for the selected month
  - Pie chart + legend with ₹ amounts and percentages
  - Use the month chips at the top (Jan–Dec) to switch months

  Monthly Trend (bar chart)
  - Shows income (green bars) vs expenses (red bars) for all 12 months of the year
  - List below shows each month's income, expenses, and net
  - Good for spotting which months you overspent

  By Person (pie chart)
  - Shows how much each family member spent in the selected month
  - Pie chart + cards per person with name, total ₹ spent, and % of total household spending

  ---
  Side Drawer (hamburger menu)

  Swipe from the left or tap the top-left icon to open the drawer. It has shortcuts to:
  - Dashboard
  - Monthly View — direct link to the current month's day-by-day view
  - Add Transaction
  - Budget Planning
  - Reports
  - Logout

  ---
  Recommended flow for each month:
  1. Start of month → go to Planning, set targets for the month (or Copy Previous)
  2. Throughout the month → tap + each time you spend or receive income
  3. End of month → check Dashboard to see actual vs planned, check Reports to see where money went
